      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs documented with sources; aleatory variability in flow rate and speed characterised by probability distributions derived from clinical operating data.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rate and impeller speed are the primary model inputs; their variability is characterised by normal distributions (flow: 4.5 ± 0.4 L/min; speed: 3000 ± 150 RPM) derived from 200-patient CPB clinical records. Blood viscosity and hematocrit are assigned fixed nominal values consistent with device labelling. A Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation across 1000 samples was executed and is referenced in the UQ report. The UQ report narrative notes that a screening sensitivity study was performed to identify dominant drivers; shear-stress exposure time emerged as a potentially influential parameter. However, no structured sensitivity analysis artefact is linked in this package. Input characterisation at Gradation 2 is considered met based on the distributional documentation alone."
